    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The Prophet Muhammad (SAWW) instructs his followers that adherence to his religion, path, and sunnah necessitates recognizing the superiority of the Imams from Ahl al-Bayt over the rest of the Muslim community. He compares them to the 'Gate of Remission' (Bab Hitta) that God commanded the Children of Israel to enter in humility for forgiveness (Quran 2:58), implying that allegiance to the Imams is a gateway to divine mercy and salvation. This hadith was narrated through a Qummi-Kufi chain via the Companion Ibn 'Abbas.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الائمة": "The Imams - the divinely appointed leaders from the Prophet's household",
          "أهل بيتي": "My Ahl al-Bayt - the Prophet's household, referring to his family lineage",
          "باب حطة": "Gate of Remission (Bab Hitta) - a gate the Children of Israel were told to enter humbly for forgiveness, referenced in Quran 2:58",
          "منهاجي": "My path (minhaj) - the clear way or methodology of the Prophet",
          "تفضيل": "Superiority/preference - recognizing the higher station of the Imams"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet Muhammad say about the Imams of Ahl al-Bayt and the Gate of Remission?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "نبی کریم (صلی اللہ علیہ وآلہ) نے فرمایا کہ جو ان کے دین، راستے اور سنت کی پیروی کرے اسے ائمہ اہل بیت کی فضیلت تسلیم کرنی چاہیے۔ آپ نے ان کا مقام باب حطہ سے تشبیہ دیا جو بنی اسرائیل کے لیے بخشش کا دروازہ تھا۔",
